718115f-a.text:
Carmine Street, north from Bedford Street. Before Seventh Avenue South was cut in 1915, Carmine Street was the connecting link between the northern end of Varick Street and the southern end of Sixth Avenue. At one time the Varick Street surface line continued over Carmine Street to and up Sixth Avenue.
April 3, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
Carmine St., n.e., from Bedford St. Neg. A-111
P.L. Sperr, photographer  May 14, 1941
